G) LOCATE  /  INSTR
=======================



— Locate Gives us the Location where the Word or the String is located in the below example [Hello is 5 Char and there is a space after that so it means World is 7th Character]

[Locate is like Simple English it means What is the Position of ‘World’  in ‘Hello World’]


SELECT LOCATE('WORLD', 'Hello World') AS position;

+----------+
| position |
+----------+
|        7 |
+----------+








— INSTR Gives us the Location where the Word or the String is located in the below example [Hello is 5 Char and there is a space after that so it means World is 7th Character]

[INSTR means in ‘Hello World’ What is the Position of the word ‘World’]


SELECT INSTR('Hello World', 'World') AS position;

+----------+
| position |
+----------+
|        7 |
+----------+




— IMP Note - We can either use LOCATE or INSTR they both are same.












— SUBSTR - When we want to Extract a Sub-string from a string we can use SUBSTR. In the Below Eg we have Extracted Cust_Street_num from Cust_Street

SUBSTR requires 3 things [COLUMN_NAME, FROM where we want to START & Till where we WANT to GO]


SELECT *, SUBSTR(customer_street,1,LOCATE(' ',customer_street)-1) AS street_number FROM customers LIMIT 20;

